SUPPLEMENTARY INFORMATION:

 Experience in program administration and outside audit findings have indicated that regulatory amendments are
needed to define with greater clarity the programs provided under this part. A primary purpose of the amendments is
to provide clear, concise guidelines that will effect a reduction in eligibility error rates. 


Amendments are being made in 25 CFR 20.1, Definitions; 20.2, Purpose; 20.3, Policy; 20.20, General and 20.23 Miscellaneous
Assistance. 
The following new sections are added: 20.15, Reporting requirements for all social services programs; 20.16, Staffing
requirements; 20.26, Adult care assistance program; 20.27, Work experience program; and 20.35, Quality assurance
reviews. 

